Text:
Good thing the gymnasium was available. I was almost
sure the Sports Club would be using it.

It seems Delta and Zeta's duels...are known for
being rather violent. They probably ran off so
they don't end up as collateral damage...

They also freed up the space when they saw me...
I'm a bit of a VIP... Eheh.

Not sure whether I'd put that on your own bad rep or
the infamy of the Photography Club... Either way, I
guess being a troublemaker has its perks.
What's that supposed to mean...?

Anyway, let's set that topic aside for now.
It looks like they're about to start.

You fine doing this with basketball? I'm pretty sure
that's what they were doing in PE today.
Anything works! I'm gonna mess you up!

(Basketball... I'm guessing that's some kind of
competitive game? This would be a good time
to look it up on my smartphone...)

Since this is between the two of us, it'll be
one-on-one. First to 10 points wins.
(One-on-one...)

(Interesting. These seem like quite the intricate
rules... The players take turns on offense and
defense, and the first to reach the determined
number of points wins.)
So who's on offense first?
Me, of course!
Okay. Let's get this over with.
Alright then... Gyaaaaagh!!!
...Oof!
She just shook Zeta off?!
Hyaaaaah!!!
Whoa, a slam dunk! She can really jump.

Finely planned strategy might be meaningless in the
face of overwhelming power and speed...
First point! I'm awesome!
Yeah, yeah. My turn now.
Heh-heh! I'm gonna stop you dead in your tracâ€”
Here goes.
Aaaaaah!!!
A shot from that far?!
...And it's good. Threes are worth two points, huh.
Grrr...! Scoring points without moving is cheating!

Aww, is the underdog whining? Basketball isn't all
just muscling your way to the basket, you know.
Grrrr...! Ball! Now!
I'm good...and I'm not gonna lose!
...Honestly, this hasn't gone how I imagined at all.

Delta can only get one point at a time... Meanwhile
Zeta gets two in one go... I assumed the latter
would have the advantage, but now...
Oops.
Another miss! Now I can catch up to you!

Eight to nine... Zeta has the lead, but things
aren't looking good. Her fickle nature is
beginning to show itself...

Yeah, her successful shot rate is clearly dropping.
She did switch to normal shots along the way, but
then went back to threes right away...
Maybe she...just doesn't like to run...?
...That may be true.
GRAAAAAAGH!!!
Whoa...?!
Hmph! Now it's nine to nine!!!
So now we have a tie...

Don't worry. Zeta is next on offense. If she makes
this shotâ€”
Okay... Oops, botched that one.
...She missed...

Yeah! Three fried noodle rolls, coming my way!
This is the lastâ€”
Huh?
The bell... School's out for the day.

All students on the premises please leave at once.
Once again, all students on the premisesâ€”

Looks like we're out of time. Too bad, guess we're
gonna have to call it here for today...
Hey, are you trying to weasel out of this?!

Not at all. I'm just trying to leave since the
school is closing. You don't want to get in
trouble either, do you?
That's true...but then what about our game?

It's nine to nine, so I s'pose that makes it a draw.
See ya.

Phew... That means I don't have to buy any fried
noodle rolls...!

But we didn't get Delta to join the club...
It would've been very reassuring to have
someone with that kind of physical ability
on our side.
Do you really need me that much?
Y-Yes... We would really welcome your help.
Then I'll join this Photography Club! So be happy!
Huh? Why the sudden change of opinion?

Heheheh, because I'm smart! It's better if I stay
close until we finish our business so she can't get
away!

O-Oh... Well, whatever the reason, I'm glad you're
joining up.

In a club with Delta, huh... Sounds like a real
pain, but I suppose I can put up with it for you.

Well, Eta? Are you fine with the three of us joining
your club?

...Yeah. It's going to get a little...no, a lot
noisier...but I can stomach it if this keeps
the club from getting shut down.

(She's scowling while she says it, but maybe...this
is a step in the right direction?)
